caption: (Translated by Google) I ordered a seafood bowl by delivery. The rice is solid and the freshness is good. Satisfied.  (Original) デリバリーで海鮮丼を注文。しっかりしたごはん、鮮度もいい感じです。満足。

I love, love, love Sakana. I order the chirashi nearly every week, it’s delicious. I also always order one of their signature rolls. I can’t pick a favorite, they are all such interesting and delicious flavor combinations. Prices are super reasonable. My neighborhood go-to.
Rice in sushi was terrible, had to use fork - the rice was falling apart

The Sakana maki was mouth watering good and I would come back for this alone. But I love to judge a sushi place by the simple staples - their California roll and their spicy tuna - both super fresh and simply amazing at this place. We got takeout and covid precautions were very satisfactory - they had the place running on point with a clear system in place.
Amazing sushi and the price is really low compared with quality
Phenomenal! The service is unparalleled, and the sushi is the best I’ve had in Boston. Undecided? As for suggestions! My new go to spot. Try it out!

Excellent sushi, best in Cambridge. They’ve done an amazing job maintaining quality through the switch to take out service during the pandemic, looking forward to dining there when things are back to normal.

Best sushi in Cambridge! Since my last post we’ve ordered from here 4x times!  DELICIOUS sushi! We ordered take-out and had such a fantastic freshly made meal that made our night! We cannot wait to keep ordering from here. Thank you so much the team who prepared this!
Got takeout and the fish was very fresh and prices were great. Definitely going back/ordering again
We ordered teriyaki and sushi for delivery, and both were amazing. Also, the packaging was fantastic!
Continuing to be the best sushi take out in all of Boston.

Very good food. Slightly smaller menu than other sushi restaurants, but what’s on it is very good and has some unique takes on traditional items. Very good, personable service. Always worth the wait. Love this place!

I ordered take out and would say the food is good. But what was outstanding to me was the service, our delivery driver unfortunately didn’t speak English and the people at the store helped ensure we still got our food and was helpful even though we all got a refund.  We definitely see the thoughtfulness in the way they treat their clients and it shows in their food. We’ll definitely be trying to eat there in person soon.  5/5 customer service
this is perhaps my favorite sushi spot!

I've eat sushi in Japan and at multiple Michelin Stars rated Omakase places in New York, LA, etc. Sushi is my favorite food. The Hamachi nigiri at Sakana is the best piece of sushi I've ever eaten. It's not fussy. It's not fancy. It is EXACTLY what excellent nigiri should be. The ratio of fish to rice and the size of the bite is perfect (please don't change a thing about that). The fish is perfectly cut and super fresh. It's a perfect bite of food and well-priced. Used to go to Ittoku for sushi but they've been slipping. This is my new go to. The rolls were good but the nigiri stole the show.  Edit: I don't get this place. I went back the day after the last review for lunch and the sushi was atrocious. It was unrecognizable compared to what I had the Sunday night before.  The fish was cut in a skimpy way and had tendons in it. Way too much rice compared to fish in the nigiri. I'd give it a 2/5. I figured that it MUST have been different folks in the kitchen so I ordered on another Sunday evening. Again, it was like a different restarant. Not nearly as bad as the Monday lunch but nowhere near as good as two weeks ago. The fish was watery and looked like it was cut down it's length for some reason (to make it shape better to the rice? I have no idea.). It was maybe a 3/5. So I'm changing my review from a 5 to a 4. Consistency is so key for a restaurant. I'd much rather frequent an OK place that is consistent than someplace which alternates between being amazing and meh. Whoever was making sushi the night of April 5, make sure to hold to that person's standards and this place will be a gem. I'm gonna hold off a few moths until I try this place again.

I just had Sakana for the first time and I can't stop gushing over how good it was.  The hamachi and salmon nigiri were two of the best pieces of sushi I've ever had.  I can't wait to eat sushi from here again.

One of the best sushi spots in Boston! The staff is always very friendly, and the sushi is always fresh and flavorful. I love how the different nigri each have their own unique taste. Definitely a must-try in Cambridge!
This spot never fails to deliver. They serve great food for affordable pricing, there is no waiting time even when they are full.
Superb sushi.
Delicious. Got Tsunami and Dragon makimoto. Partner got the lunch special, which was substantial (salad and miso soup not pictured).
great place. No frills, simple in the best way: fresh food and good service.

I came here with a friend on a weekday night, and we were immediately seated upon arrival and given menus and served water. There were a lot of options on the menu, but I eventually decided on the Hokkaido and Dragon. One of them had seared scallop on it which was delicious which gave the entire roll a roast-y seared flavor and it was awesome; I've never had sushi like that before. Both rolls were really fresh, and I liked all the ingredients in both. I really enjoyed my meal, and service was pretty good too. The rolls came out to be around $30 post-tax which is a bit pricey, but for the quality, I would go again.
There are many interesting combinations, including a delicious truffle based sushi

Let me stop you right there. By far one of the best sushi restaurant near Boston. Very humble atmosphere but the food is amazing. Super high quality fish and great display. Definitely coming back to try different items.
Great sushi
I eat in this spot a lot since I work close by. I got to say their service is always awesome and they keep the place clean constantly. Prices are reasonable and they serve generous portions.
Loved this sushi place. The service was great and the food is even better. The sashimi were good quality and nice and thick. The rolls are also delicious, no cheap imitation crab whatsoever!
Affordable and really tasty, fresh sushi. I did not love the Hokkaido special roll.
Excellent sushi! Best sushi I have had in the Boston area! It a small place, so make sure to make a reservation or go early to get a table on busier days
Very fresh Sushi. Pleasant and efficient staff. Very limited food, beer and wine menu. Very small establishment. What they do, they do WELL.
Omg amazing. So yummy. And the people are so nice!!
Got the Nigiri Dinner, has 6 sushi rolls and 6 chef's choice of sashimi. They were all amazing. Tries sashimi for the first time, and loved it, inspire of being sceptical about eating raw meat.
Fresh fish! High quality sushi! A surprising find!
Definitely my go to Cambridge sushi place. High quality fish, fast preparation, friendly service and reasonable prices. Not a lot not to love.
Best sushi food I've ever had

The prices are fair -- even better than fair -- the fish fresh and the staff amazing.  My new favorite lunch spot.  I seldom review but I want to support them.  A wonderful addition to the neighborhood!
Wow! Amazing sushi. So tasty. Had an amazing time with my wife on a Sunday afternoon. Service was excellent. The food was even better and at affordable prices. Highly recommended. We will be back.
Excellent, fresh food.
Good sushi place, inexpensive and for the seared options quite tasty

The prices at this place for the size/portions are absolutely abysmal. Ended up paying about $10 for a tiny, stand alone portion of salmon roe. I also ordered a crimson roll (one of their specials) which you’d think would be a larger piece of sushi. Each piece was smaller than the sushi you’d get at 7/11 or something. Though the quality of everything was good, the prices compared to the sizes absolutely suck.
Amazing sushi in a very cozy and nice location.
Great Sushi, try the black forest, fair prices, good service
This place is incredible. Great menu, amazing service, amazing sushi.

So glad to have this in my neighborhood! I came for dinner with a couple friends recently, and we were pretty happy with our meal. They both got the salmon rice, and I got the crimson roll. It was really good with a variety of contrasting textures, but I wasn't yet full so I also got a steamed gyoza. Spent about $16-18 per person. The servers are also very professional and nice. Would recommend stopping by!
Food was good but a little bit expensive considering the amount of food.
Good quality for the price, a good local spot if you want to have sushi.
One of the best rolls I have had is their signature  roll.
This is my absolute favorite sushi in cambridge. The Sakana sushi is amazing! The staff is super friendly! Best sushi place in town!
Small place with great sushi and good service. We had the sashimi and niguiri dinners and everything was great.
Great service and amazing food!!
The fish is very good and the people are very nice.  The menu is not adventuresome but quality is very good for the price.
Easily amongst the best few sushi options in Boston/Cambridge.
Completely by chance stumbled on some of the best sushi I’ve ever had. Didn’t read the reviews before I came in, this inconspicuous restaurant took me by surprise and made my day!
Lovely food. Lovely price. Lovely restaurant and people.
This place is the best sushi in Cambridge and Boston! Seared Salmon belly is deadly! GO!
Great sushi, small area.
Fresh food, excellent service, delicious tea. Best sushi in Cambridge.
Delicious and unique sushi. Extremely attentive service. A little small and very popular right now since it’s new. Prices are about what you’d expect for good sushi, which is a little expensive.
Sakana thank you for making lots of people at this Super Bowl party happy! I barely put it on the table and heard, "there's sushi?!" They loved it :)
love the chef, so cute
Very fresh and awesome service! Will definitely be back.
Excellent rolls. Great sashimi.

The sushi here is real good! I ordered a spicy salmon roll and a Sakana roll. The spicy tuna was pretty simple as expected, but still tasty. The signature roll was way more flavorful and complex than the basic roll, so there's definitely value to paying twice as much per roll. The presentation of the sushi was also on point.  The staff were non-intrusive and very kind! The space is small, but nice. I definitely would recommend this place if you're looking for sushi in the area.
That was a really nice spot for dinner, tasty and chill... :)
Abusolitely perfect. I had the best Uni and Sushi here.
The Sakura making roll is my favorite thus far.
I just came back from lunch at Sakana and to be hones...it was the best sushi I have had in Boston in years. It was so delicious that I want to go back tomorrow!

Great for dinner or lunch, dine-in or take-out. I've been to this place twice (it's only been open for a short time) and each time was a very pleased with the experiences overall. The food has very tasty and they readily accommodated our food allergies. It is a small space, which allows the staff to be doting yet not overbearing. It has only been open for about a month and it is already our go-to sushi place in the area.

I enjoyed my visit to this new restaurant. My husband and I shared a delicious sushi roll with fresh salmon, and then we each got a bento box. Everything was delicious and the wait staff was very friendly.  I really like how they have made this space look so nice.

Perhaps I was unfortunate, but the food was plain bad. Stale sashimi pieces (couple looked like leftovers from yesterday), tasteless ama-ebi, wilted daikon and salad. The only good looking thing was a small cup of rice.
This place is fantastic. Wish it was open while I was a student. Will be back when I visit again.
Great new sushi place. Reasonable prices, friendly service, delicious food.
Super nice owners, cute but casual environment, tasty sushi at affordable price! Try the green rice tea and spicy edamame!
